          <title>Minneapolis headed for potential 'never-ending loop' in community safety commissioner nomination</title>
          <description><![CDATA[The Minneapolis City Council and Mayor Jacob Frey are in a disagreement over whether to reappoint current commissioner Todd Barnette to another term. The city attorney says they could be at a standstill, without votes to either overturn a mayoral veto or confirm Barnette’s appointment.]]></description>
